li.font: Learned index based database as the main database. (EurusDB will go).
Each stateful solver will have a primary key, that indicates the space where it should store the data.
In the secondary node, an abstract can be generated, and used for calculating distance and perform spatial search. The abstract is used and called as secondary key.
A bi-map is created between the key and the abstract. So that with an abstract, we can find the index and therefore the data.

li.span: The database should be contained in a docker container, and communicated with AID solvers through http request. (It will needs some configuration on the network).

li.font: It is ok to store the data in memory, but a docker volume would be preferred. It can be in memory, and persisted periodically.
It requires all AID solvers to be on the same network. It should be done earlier.
